<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-01-15T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-01-15T10:00:00-05:00" n="171" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">700.00116 M.E./64: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-01-15T18:00:00+03:00">January
                                    15, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>59. After 10 days replete with evasions, obstructions, and delays exit
                            visas were finally issued this afternoon to Rassmussen, the Hansons,
                            Millers and Owens. As an example of the tactics employed, Rodman’s exit
                            visa is being withheld by the Soviet authorities pending an extension of
                            his permit to reside in the Soviet Union which has expired since his
                            arrival in Moscow. I hope to be able to obtain Rodman’s exit visa within
                            the next 2 or 3 days.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>